<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="

&gt;Can anyone tell me how to find info on cleaning cast iron kitchen
items?
&gt;Thank you!

"/> Ask a grandma but don't let her convince you to toss the skillet in the
fireplace! This method does work but it is risky at best and Murphy's
law will surely come into play with your most expensive items and cause
them to warp or crack.

A better way that does not take any special tools is to put your
skillets in a self cleaning oven and use the controlled heat to burn
off the gook. Be sure to remove any wood handles first!

After that, it's just a matter of scrubbing off the ash with a
stainless steel scrub pad and lots of soap an water. (note: don't use
the brass or copper scrub pads because they will rub off on the iron)

Good luck
GH

